  "local_port": 47098,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What can I include in areas of interests in my resume?",
  "response": "When including areas of interest in your resume, it's important to list items that are relevant to the job you're applying for, showcase your personality, and highlight your skills and passions. Here are some examples of what you can include:\n\n1. Professional development: Mention any relevant workshops, conferences, or certifications that you're interested in pursuing.\n\n2. Industry-specific topics: Include areas within your field that you're passionate about, such as digital marketing, data analysis, or sustainable design.\n\n3. Technology: List any software, programming languages, or tools that you're interested in learning or have experience with.\n\n4. Hobbies and extracurricular activities: Mention hobbies that demonstrate skills relevant to the job, such as team sports, volunteering, or creative pursuits like photography or writing.\n\n5. Community involvement: Include any organizations or causes you're passionate about and actively involved in, such as environmental conservation or social justice initiatives.\n\n6. Continuing education: If you're interested in furthering your education, mention any relevant courses or degree programs you plan to pursue.\n\nWhen listing your areas of interest, keep the following tips in mind:\n\n- Be specific and concise, using bullet points to make your interests easy to read.\n- Tailor your interests to the job you're applying for, focusing on those that align with the company's values and the position's requirements.\n- Keep your list short, ideally between 3-5 items, to maintain the reader's attention.\n- Use professional language and avoid mentioning controversial or potentially divisive topics.\n\nRemember, your areas of interest can help you stand out from other candidates and give potential employers a better understanding of who you are as a person and a professional.",
